CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 9, 1951, pg. 23, reads: "Friendship Chapter 69 OES Tea - When Friendship Chapter 69, Order of Eastern Star, held its tea last Sunday, the following persons were present: First row, left to right: Dorothy Wells, Associate Matron; George Crumpton, Worthy Patron; Elizabeth McKenzie, Worthy Matron and Grand Chairman of the Youth Circle of Pennsylvania. Second row: Lillian Williams, Martha; Verna Bush, Electra; Edythe Barrow, Esther; Elizabeth Little, Associate Conductress; Virginia Rice, Ruth, and Jennie Cissell, Adah.  Third row: Josephine Davis, Financial Secretary; Hattie Taylor, Juanita Means, Elizabeth Charlie, Mamie Butler, Eheresa Seabrooks, Treasurer; May F. Thompson, Rhoda Marks, Recorder; Ada Redmon and Estella Bailey. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Friendship Chapter 69, Order of Eastern Star, from left, first row: Dorothy Wells, George Crumpton, and Elizabeth McKenzie; second row: Lillian Williams, Verna Bush, Edythe Barrow, Elizabeth Little, Virginia Rice, and Jennie Cissell; third row: Josephine Davis, Hattie Taylor, Juanita Means, Elizabeth Charlie, Mamie Butler, Eheresa Seabrooks, May F. Thompson, Rhoda Marks, Ada Redmon, and Estella Bailey, gathered behind table with two tiered cake during tea, in interior
